FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31605
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1776211372
OL,3,CWhat is 'Super El Nino' and could it
OL,4,Cmake this summer much hotter?
OL,6,FAt it's most ramped up, this event is
OL,7,Freferred to as La Nina where the warm
OL,8,Fpool of water to the west is larger
OL,9,Fand warmer than normal and the cooler
OL,10,Fwater to the east is colder and also
OL,11,Flarger than usual.
OL,13,FHowever, every few years, those trade
OL,14,Fwinds weaken, which allow those warmer
OL,15,Fwaters to drift back towards the east
OL,16,F- a change that is called El Nino.
OL,26,@kD@UTwoD@UTwxD@`Tw
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,317,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31606
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F316A1776211372
OL,3,CWhat is 'Super El Nino' and could it
OL,4,Cmake this summer much hotter?
OL,6,FThis pool of warmer water shifting
OL,7,Feastwards means that the rising warm
OL,8,Fair/evaporating/condensing cycle that
OL,9,Fgenerated rain towards the western
OL,10,FPacific instead shifts towards South
OL,11,FAmerica.
OL,13,FWithout this rain, droughts and
OL,14,Fheatwaves in particular are more
OL,15,Flikely towards Australasia.
OL,26,@kD@UTw
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
